  <Docs since="1">
    <summary>Interface for releasing a connection.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">Interface for releasing a connection.
 This can be implemented by various "trigger" objects which are
 associated with a connection, for example
 a <c><see cref="T:Org.Apache.Http.Conn.EofSensorInputStream" /></c>
 or an <c><see cref="T:Org.Apache.Http.Conn.BasicManagedEntity" /></c>
 or the <c><see cref="T:Org.Apache.Http.Conn.IManagedClientConnection" /></c> itself.
 <format type="text/html"><br /></format>
 The methods in this interface can safely be called multiple times.
 The first invocation releases the connection, subsequent calls
 are ignored.</para>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">
        <format type="text/html">
          <a href="http://developer.android.com/reference/org/apache/http/conn/ConnectionReleaseTrigger.html" target="_blank">[Android Documentation]</a>
        </format>
      </para>
    </remarks>
    <since version="Added in API level 1" />
  </Docs>
